name: roasted green bean medley with avocado vinaigrette
instructions:
1. Preheat oven to 425 degrees F.

2. Coat a roasting pan with cooking spray.

3. In a large bowl, toss green beans, shallots, canola oil, and black pepper. 

4. Spread green beans on roasting pan and roast for 10-12 minutes, or until green beans start to brown, stirring a few times during cooking process.

5. While beans are cooking, cut 3 halves of avocado into cubes (save remaining avocado half for dressing.) Put into small bowl and toss with lemon juice to keep from browning. Set aside.

6. To make dressing, add to blender (or use hand blender) remaining avocado half, olive oil, vinegar, and mustard. 

7. Process until smooth and thick. Add 1 or 2 tablespoons of water to thin out the dressing to your liking.

8. To serve, arrange green beans on a serving plate and place cubed avocados on top. Drizzle with avocado dressing.
